   <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-2">1. Introduction</h3>
   <p class="mb-6">This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, and share information from users who use our app FiestUp.com ("Service") to create and join music parties through Spotify. We are committed to protecting your privacy and handling your data transparently.</p>

   <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-2">2. Commitments to Privacy</h3>
   <p class="mb-6">We are committed to:</p>
   <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-6">
     <li>Respecting the privacy of our users and processing personal data with consent.</li>
     <li>Processing only the personal data strictly necessary for providing the requested service, securely and confidentially.</li>
     <li>Not using personal data for purposes without prior consent.</li>
     <li>Not sharing personal data with third parties.</li>
     <li>Retaining personal data only for the time necessary for its specific purpose.</li>
   </ul>

   <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-2">3. Information We Collect</h3>
   <p class="mb-4">When you log in to Spotify to create a party, we collect the following information:</p>
   <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-6">
     <li><strong>User ID</strong>: Unique identifier for your Spotify account.</li>
     <li><strong>Email</strong>: Used for account verification and authentication.</li>
     <li><strong>Username, Account Type, and Profile Image</strong>: For display within the Service.</li>
     <li><strong>Access and Refresh Tokens</strong>: To maintain your session with Spotify and enable functionality like playback control.</li>
   </ul>

   <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-2">4. How We Use Your Information</h3>
   <p class="mb-4">We use the data collected to:</p>
   <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-6">
     <li>Authenticate and verify accounts.</li>
     <li>Control playback in parties.</li>
     <li>Display user profiles and facilitate collaboration in music parties.</li>
     <li>Maintain user sessions with Spotify.</li>
   </ul>
   <p class="mb-6">We do not share any personal data with third-party services or partners. All data is retained solely within the Service.</p>

   <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-2">5. Legal Basis for Data Processing</h3>
   <p class="mb-6">The legal basis for processing your personal data is your consent, as provided when you log in with Spotify and interact with the Service.</p>

   <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-2">6. Your Rights over Your Data</h3>
   <p class="mb-4">As a user, you may exercise the following rights:</p>
   <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-6">
     <li><strong>Right of Access</strong>: Request confirmation on whether we are processing your personal data and access it if we are.</li>
     <li><strong>Right of Rectification</strong>: Request corrections to your personal data if inaccurate.</li>
     <li><strong>Right of Erasure</strong>: Request deletion of your personal data at any time.</li>
     <li><strong>Right to Data Portability</strong>: Request transfer of your data to another data controller, where feasible.</li>
     <li><strong>Right to Restrict Processing</strong>: Request suspension of processing while a verification takes place, such as when contesting data accuracy.</li>
   </ul>
   <p class="mb-6">You may exercise these rights by contacting us at the email provided in this policy. If you feel your rights are violated, you may also file a complaint with the Spanish Data Protection Agency (Agencia Española de Protección de Datos).</p>

   <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-2">7. Data Retention and Deletion</h3>
   <p class="mb-4"><strong>Automatic Session Deletion</strong>: Sessions expire and are automatically deleted every three days.</p>
   <p class="mb-6"><strong>User-Initiated Deletion</strong>: You can delete your account at any time within the app. This will permanently remove all personal data, including Spotify information and any parties you created.</p>

   <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-2">8. Data Security</h3>
   <p class="mb-6">We take reasonable precautions to protect your information, using technical and organizational measures to prevent unauthorized access, accidental loss, or damage. All collected data, including tokens, is securely stored and accessed only as necessary for providing the Service.</p>

   <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-2">9. Sharing of Personal Data with Third Parties</h3>
   <p class="mb-6">No personal data will be shared with third parties unless required by law. We do not anticipate international data transfers.</p>

   <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-2">10. Changes to this Privacy Policy</h3>
   <p class="mb-6">We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. If we make significant changes, we will notify you. Continued use of the Service after changes signifies acceptance of the updated policy.</p>

   <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-2">11. Contact Information</h3>
   <p class="contact font-semibold text-blue-700">For questions or concerns about this Privacy Policy, please contact us at help@fiestup.com.</p>
